Agreed. I wrote a reply to your post thanking you for taking action. I reiterated that there was no way I was going to respond to such a post's claims. To leave such an offensive post standing however would be inviting responses from newcomers who would not (for lack of a response from me) know how much of the post was true and how much was fabricated. I therefore asked that you delete the content of the offensive post then replace it with something to the effect of &quot;edited&quot;. After posting this request I realised that Yales had taken it upon himself to delete your reprimand of his behaviour, his flaming/spamming and several of my own posts. Then he wrote his own biased account of where the censored posts had gone. None of the posts by you or I contained offensive material and therefore this is a clear abuse of moderator powers. He was the violator. He had no right to touch other posts by innocent members. I think we should start looking for a new moderator. We can't have somebody deleting other members posts without justification. <br>
